The defendant Paden Robert Valentine was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Drive or Operate Vehicle w/o Consent, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

9:17 AM Defendant Paden Robert Valentine in court.  Attorney Jaramy J Hansen in court for Paden Robert Valentine.  Attorney Mark Adam Fruehauf in court for State of Wisconsin. Parties indicate agreement. State asks that sentence be withheld for 2 years of probation. Conditions of no conditional jail, 3 days credit; costs, DOC programming, continuation of no contact with Victim. Parties ask that the court finds the defendant will be eligible for expungement upon successful completion of probation.
Defendant pleads no contest. Attorney Johansen stipulates to a factual basis. Court finds the defendant's pleas have been knowingly and voluntarily made, Court accepts the defendant's plea and finds the defendant guilty.
Court orders withheld sentence for 2 years of probation. Conditions of 3 days jail with 3 days credit, payment of court costs, DOC programming, and continuation no contact with Victim. Defendant will be eligible for expungement upon successful completion of probation. Successful completion of probation includes payment of all financial obligations in full.
